By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Monday confirmed 157 new cases of #COVID-19 in Nigeria. The report released via it’s twitter handle account said the fresh infections brought the total confirmed cases to 65,305 out of which 61,162 patients have been discharged from various isolation facilities across the country. The health agency stated that the 157 cases were recorded from 9 out of the 36 states of the federation as follows: Lagos-97Oyo-37Kaduna -9Bayelsa-3Edo-3Ekiti-3Ondo-2Osun-2Plateau-1 The NCDC further reported that 1,163 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case on 27th February 2020. The state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases is shown below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -   The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it has confirmed 111 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. This new cases, it said, brought total Confirmed COVID-19 infections in Nigeria to 57,724 out of which 48,985 patients have been discharged. According to… September 24, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria's confirmed COVID-19 infections figure shrunk to  58 new cases on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has said. According to the report released by the NCDC, the newly recorded cases brought the total confirmed cases to 59,345 out of which… October 5, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 152 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. According to the report released via it's twitter handle late Tuesday, this brings total confirmed cases 64,336 out ot which 60,333 have been treated and discharged from various isolation… November 11, 2020 In "Top Stories"